---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import BitDiagram from "../components/BitDiagram.astro";
import BitLegend from "../components/BitLegend.astro";
---

<Base 
  title="Encoding Reference" 
  description="RISC-V instruction encoding formats: R-type, I-type, S-type, B-type, U-type, J-type. Learn how RISC-V instructions are encoded in 32-bit formats."
  keywords="risc-v encoding, riscv encoding, risc-v instruction format, R-type, I-type, S-type, B-type, U-type, J-type, risc-v opcode, riscv funct3, riscv funct7"
>
  <h1>Encoding Reference</h1>
  <p>All RISC-V instructions are 32 bits wide and follow one of six encoding formats.</p>

  <BitLegend />

  <br>
  <h3>R-type (Register)</h3>
  <p class="type-desc">Used for register-to-register operations like <code>ADD</code>, <code>SUB</code>, <code>AND</code>, <code>OR</code>.</p>
  <BitDiagram type="R" />
  <div class="half-space"></div>

  <h3>I-type (Immediate)</h3>
  <p class="type-desc">Used for immediate operations and loads: <code>ADDI</code>, <code>LW</code>, <code>JALR</code>.</p>
  <BitDiagram type="I" />
  <div class="half-space"></div>

  <h3>S-type (Store)</h3>
  <p class="type-desc">Used for store instructions: <code>SW</code>, <code>SH</code>, <code>SB</code>.</p>
  <BitDiagram type="S" />
  <div class="half-space"></div>

  <h3>B-type (Branch)</h3>
  <p class="type-desc">Used for conditional branches: <code>BEQ</code>, <code>BNE</code>, <code>BLT</code>.</p>
  <BitDiagram type="B" />
  <div class="half-space"></div>

  <h3>U-type (Upper Immediate)</h3>
  <p class="type-desc">Used for <code>LUI</code> and <code>AUIPC</code> (loading upper 20 bits).</p>
  <BitDiagram type="U" />
  <div class="half-space"></div>

  <h3>J-type (Jump)</h3>
  <p class="type-desc">Used for <code>JAL</code> (jump and link).</p>
  <BitDiagram type="J" />
</Base>

<style>
  h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .type-desc {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
</style>
